## 13. Examples

### Example A: Allowed Personal Use

A user studies the OPRMT™ Framework Standard and uses the sequence privately to improve personal ChatGPT prompts.

Status: Generally allowed.

### Example B: Allowed Public Reference

A blogger writes an article explaining different prompt engineering frameworks and mentions OPRMT™ with attribution.

Status: Generally allowed with attribution.

### Example C: Review Required

A consultant wants to use OPRMT™ terminology in paid client prompt engineering packages.

Status: Review required.

### Example D: Permission Required

A creator wants to sell an OPRMT™ prompt pack based on repository templates.

Status: Permission required.

### Example E: Not Allowed Without Approval

A company copies OPRMT™ files, removes ownership notices, renames the framework, and sells it as its own training system.

Status: Not allowed.

